HEADWORD: Corosso
<hw>Co*ros"so</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(k?-r?"th? ⟦or⟧ -s?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>cerozo</ets> a kind of palm tree.]</ety> <def>The name in Central
America for the seed of a true palm; also, a commercial name for the
true ivory nut. See <er>Ivory nut</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

